26quot%3Bto%20learning%20from%20this%20experience%20to%20ensure%20greater%20sensitivity%20and%20understanding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BYour%20forgiveness%20is%20important%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20am%20committed%20to%20making%20amends%20and%20promoting%20unity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20title%20track%20on%20Ye's%20latest%20album%2C%20%26quot%3BVultures%26quot%3B%20references%20his%20earlier%20comments%20with%20the%20lyric%3A%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EHow%20I'm%20antisemitic%3F%20I%20just%20fucked%20a%20Jewish%20bitch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-kanye-west-apologizes-jewish-community-instagram-post-antisemitic-outbursts-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703586071000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65210d216561dd877e73f140%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-kanye-west-apologizes-jewish-community-instagram-post-antisemitic-outbursts-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rapper%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Kanye%20West%2C%20published%20an%20apology%20in%20Hebrew%20to%20his%20Instagram%2C%20saying%20he%20did%20not%20intend%20%26quot%3Bto%20hurt%20or%20demean.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jsommers%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Sommers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-kanye-west-apologizes-jewish-community-instagram-post-antisemitic-outbursts-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20to%20Denmark%20from%20the%20UK%20for%20better%20childcare.%20The%20lifestyle%20here%20means%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20choose%20between%20a%20job%20I%20love%20and%20my%20kids.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Laura%20Hall%2C%20a%20mom%20and%20her%20daughter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658457e1cefc010bea262dba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELaura%20Hall%20moved%20to%20Copenhagen%2C%20Denmark%2C%20with%20her%20family%20in%202017.%3Cp%3ELaura%20Hall%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELaura%20Hall%20moved%20to%20Denmark%20with%20her%20family%20in%202017%20from%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20drawn%20to%20Copenhagen%20because%20it's%20been%20ranked%20one%20of%20the%20best%20places%20to%20raise%20children.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHall%20said%20the%20commitment%20to%20%26quot%3Bhygge%26quot%3B%20and%20hands-off%20childcare%20surprised%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20I%20was%20working%20remotely%20from%20the%20UK%20as%20the%20communications%20director%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kidandcoe.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EKid%20%26amp%3B%20Coe%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20family-travel%20startup%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20was%20working%20for%20a%20company%20with%20offices%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20Knowing%20that%20the%20Brexit%20vote%20would%20narrow%20our%20chances%20of%20working%20abroad%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20live%20in%20Europe%20for%20a%20few%20years%20while%20we%20still%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20been%20to%20Copenhagen%2C%20Denmark%2C%20on%20vacation.%20The%20car-free%20culture%20was%20appealing%2C%20as%20was%20the%20chance%20to%20live%20more%20sustainably%20and%20find%20out%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20live%20in%20a%20country%20ranked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.william-russell.com%2Fblog%2Fbest-countries-to-raise-family-relocating-expat-kids%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone%20of%20the%20best%20to%20raise%20children%20in%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We'd%20also%20met%20a%20few%20Danes%20in%20our%20travels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20bought%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20the%20city%2C%20rented%20out%20our%20house%2C%20and%20left.%20Fast-forward%20nearly%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20we're%20permanent%20residents%20with%20no%20plans%20to%20return%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20permanent%20residency%20in%20Denmark%20was%20easy%2C%20as%20we%20came%20before%20the%20Brexit%20changes.%20Because%20we%20were%20European%20Union%20citizens%2C%20applying%20for%20residency%20was%20a%20formality.%20Here's%20what%20surprised%20us%20the%20most%20since%20our%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Hygge'%20culture%20is%20prioritized%20over%20hustle%20culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20people%20exaggerated%20the%20Danish%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bhygge.%26quot%3B%20Boy%2C%20was%20I%20wrong.%20Hygge%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20Danish%20concept%20of%20taking%20time%20to%20relax%20and%20enjoy%20simple%20comforts%2C%20is%20everything%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20go%20out%20for%20a%20drink%20with%20your%20friends%2C%20it's%20%26quot%3Bhyggeligt%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20it's%20fun%20and%20comforting.%20In%20the%20swimming%20pool%2C%20there's%20a%20lane%20for%20fast%20swimmers%2C%20a%20lane%20for%20medium%20swimmers%2C%20and%20a%20lane%20for%20hygge%20swimming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20cultural%20experience%3B%20the%20translation%20of%20%26quot%3Bcozy%26quot%3B%20does%20it%20justice.%20It's%20more%20about%20enjoying%20the%20moment%2C%20taking%20pleasure%20in%20each%20other's%20company%2C%20and%20prioritizing%20the%20good%20moments.%20It%20may%20be%20why%20there's%20not%20really%20hustle%20culture%20here%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0people%20don't%20typically%20prioritize%20anything%20uncomfortable%20over%20enjoying%20a%20warm%20and%20cozy%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDanish%20children%20are%20independent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20funniest%20conversations%20I%20had%20was%20with%20a%20parent%20about%20what%20to%20get%20our%20kids%20for%20Christmas.%20She%20was%20considering%20a%20hunting%20knife.%20Her%20son%20was%205.%20It%20was%20perfectly%20normal%20for%20her%20%E2%80%94%20but%20for%20me%20as%20an%20English%20mum%2C%20all%20I%20could%20think%20about%20were%20the%20safety%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Denmark%2C%20kids%20are%20much%20more%20independent%20from%20a%20younger%20age%20than%20in%20the%20UK.%20I%20often%20see%20children%20walking%20home%20alone%20from%20school%20or%20doing%20an%20activity%20at%20a%20much%20younger%20age%20than%20would%20be%20acceptable%20in%20my%20home%20country.%20Even%20in%20kindergarten%20in%20Denmark%2C%20my%20kids%20play%20next%20to%20an%20in-use%20fireplace.%20They're%20trusted%20to%20be%20independent%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20resilient%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20weather%20is%20very%20different%20from%20the%20UK's%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20we're%20just%20across%20the%20North%20Sea%20from%20the%20UK%2C%20the%20weather%20is%20very%20different%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20so%20much%20warmer%20in%20the%20summer%20and%20so%20much%20colder%20in%20the%20winter.%20Sometimes%20the%20harbor%20freezes%20in%20winter%2C%20which%20feels%20dramatic.%20In%20summer%2C%20there%20are%20weeks%20of%20nearly%20uninterrupted%20sunny%20weather%20and%20many%20sandy%20beaches%20to%20play%20on.%20We%20feel%20a%20lot%20closer%20to%20the%20weather%20than%20we%20did%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20perhaps%20because%20we%20do%20everything%20by%20bike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommunity%20is%20everything%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20word%20of%20the%20year%20in%20Denmark%20was%20%26quot%3Bsamfundssind%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcademic%20studies%20have%20cited%20Denmark's%20strong%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20the%20trust%20in%20government%20as%20reasons%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7217796%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDenmark%2520has%2520effectively%2520controlled%2520the%2Cfast%2520and%2520strict%2520lockdown%2520response.%26amp%3Btext%3DDanish%2520society%2520and%2520industry%2520slowly%2C%252Dopen%2520in%2520mid%252DApril.%26amp%3Btext%3DA%2520rapid%2520response%252C%2520trust%2520in%2Ceffective%2520management%2520of%2520Covid%252D19.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elow%20rates%20of%20infection%20and%20deaths%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20with%20other%20European%20countries.%20In%20Copenhagen%2C%20lockdowns%20were%20fast%20and%20short%20because%20people%20worked%20together%2C%20had%20a%20high%20level%20of%20trust%20in%20the%20government%20and%20authorities%2C%20and%20followed%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spirit%20of%20community%20is%20represented%20in%20the%20flat%20hierarchies%20in%20Danish%20businesses%20and%20its%20drive%20for%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20sense%20of%20community%20in%20our%20neighborhood%20and%20at%20work.%20It's%20a%20big%20positive%20of%20living%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20flip%20side%20is%20that%20it's%20sometimes%20hard%20if%20you%20stand%20out%20in%20any%20way%20%E2%80%94%20unlike%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%2C%20it%20can%20be%20frowned%20upon%20to%20be%20too%20much%20of%20an%20individual.%20And%20bragging%20about%20yourself%20or%20your%20achievements%20doesn't%20go%20down%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20not%20perfect%2C%20but%20I%20love%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20hype%20about%20Denmark%20being%20one%20of%20the%20happiest%20countries%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20that%20ignores%20a%20lot%20of%20factors.%20We've%20had%20only%20good%20experiences%20as%20English%20expats.%20That's%20sadly%20not%20the%20case%20for%20all%20our%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20undertone%20of%20sexism%20and%20racism%20that%20makes%20me%20feel%20uncomfortable%20at%20times.%20The%20drive%20for%20equality%20is%20admirable%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20work%20in%20progress%3A%20There%20are%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berlingske.dk%2Fvirksomheder%2Fder-er-stadig-flere-danske-topchefer-der-hedder-lars-eller-peter-end%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20business%20leaders%20called%20Lars%20or%20Peter%20in%20Denmark%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20female%20CEOs.%20Though%20I%20do%20see%20these%20issues%20being%20talked%20about%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20living%20in%20Copenhagen.%20I%20love%20swimming%20in%20the%20harbor%2C%20I%20love%20my%20Danish%20friends%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20internet%20will%20tell%20you%20it's%20hard%20to%20make%20Danish%20friends%20as%20an%20expat%2C%20but%20I%20disagree%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20love%20living%20in%20a%20city%20where%20everything%20is%20a%2015-minute%20cycle%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20admire%20the%20incredible%20kindness%20and%20warmth%20of%20the%20Danes%2C%20who%20are%20intimidatingly%20tall%20and%20beautiful%20but%20always%20up%20for%20a%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20a%20lifestyle%20that%20allows%20me%20to%20be%20a%20parent%20with%20happy%2C%20well-cared-for%20children%20and%20hold%20down%20a%20job%20I%20love%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Life%20just%20works%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-denmark-better-child-care-love-it-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703585876000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65845802cefc010bea262dde%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-denmark-better-child-care-love-it-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Laura%20Hall%20moved%20to%20Denmark%20in%202017%20because%20of%20the%20country's%20reputation%20as%20parent-friendly.%20She%20loves%20the%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20%26quot%3Bhygge%26quot%3B%20culture.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Laura%20Hall)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-denmark-better-child-care-love-it-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%