abits-that-stick-according-to-a-neuroscientist-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20those%20better%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20manageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Commit%20to%20forming%20habits%20by%20completing%20them%20at%20a%20certain%20time%20each%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20found%20that%20the%20earlier%20you%20do%20important%20things%20%E2%80%94%20before%20you%20have%20other%20excuses%20or%20distractions%20%E2%80%94%20the%20better.%20Even%20if%20you%20can't%20do%20something%20early%2C%20do%20it%20at%20the%20same%20time%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20form%20a%20habit%2C%20you%20must%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-millionaires-build-wealth-consistency-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommit%20to%20consistently%20doing%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20at%20least%20two%20or%20three%20weeks.%20That%20way%2C%20you%20not%20only%20form%20the%20habit%20but%20also%20have%20a%20fair%20chance%20to%20assess%20whether%20you're%20enjoying%20or%20benefiting%20from%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20this%20in%20my%20life%20by%20waking%20up%2045%20minutes%20earlier%2C%20at%205%20a.m.%2C%20to%20give%20myself%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-people-morning-reading-habits-2014-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eread%20a%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20distractions%20before%20my%20family%20wakes%20up.%20After%20the%20first%20three%20weeks%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20a%20habit%20I%20wanted%20to%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20doing%20it%20for%20the%20past%2018%20months.%20It's%20relaxing%20and%20has%20given%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20insights%2C%20as%20I'm%20reading%20a%20lot%20more%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20this%20dedicated%20%26quot%3Bme%20time%26quot%3B%20offline%20has%20also%20been%20good%20for%20my%20productivity.%20Instead%20of%20waking%20up%20and%20immediately%20looking%20at%20my%20emails%2C%20I%20start%20my%20day%20on%20my%20own%20terms%20with%20the%20help%20of%20my%20new%20habit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Set%20a%20target%20and%20work%20backward%20to%20reach%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20habit%20I%20encourage%20my%20clients%20to%20set%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-much-should-i-save-each-month%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%25%20gross%20savings%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20can%20sound%20intimidating%2C%20so%20I've%20found%20the%20best%20way%20to%20do%20this%20is%20to%20work%20backward.%20I%20got%20there%20by%20looking%20at%20expenses%20and%20later%20focusing%20on%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20my%20clients%20to%20set%20aside%2020%25%20of%20what%20they%20make%20in%20an%20account%20separate%20from%20the%20one%20they%20use%20for%20their%20main%20transactions.%20If%20a%20client%20can't%20reach%20that%2020%25%20figure%2C%20they%20either%20have%20to%20make%20more%20money%2C%20or%20we%20have%20to%20work%20on%20outflows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20I've%20found%20to%20do%20this%20is%20by%20looking%20at%20food%20expenses%20because%20they%20have%20the%20most%20meaningful%20monthly%20impact%2C%20but%20people%20tend%20to%20ignore%20them.%20If%20you%20cut%20out%20a%20streaming%20service%2C%20you%20may%20save%20%2415%20a%20month%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbudget-restaurants-cooking-groceries-eating-out-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20down%20eating%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%20nights%20a%20week%20to%20one%20can%20mean%20saving%20%24100%20or%20more%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Use%20resources%20to%20stop%20procrastination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20we%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20on%20our%20phones%2C%20we%20should%20be%20putting%20apps%20to%20work%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20suggest%20all%20my%20clients%20use%20an%20app%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.apple.com%2Fus%2