0a%20Google%20recruiter%20to%20become%20a%20full-time%20tattoo%20artist.%20It%20feels%20amazing%20and%20I'll%20never%20look%20back.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Sprague%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65816ca9a79e5746976ad0b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20Sprague%20quit%20his%20job%20as%20a%20Google%20recruiter%20to%20work%20as%20a%20full-time%20tattoo%20artist.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Sprague%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDaniel%20Sprague%20was%20a%20recruiter%20at%20Google%2C%20contracted%20via%20Adecco%2C%20and%20made%20a%20six-figure%20salary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESprague%20quit%20in%20December%202022%20ahead%20of%20layoffs%20because%20he%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20progress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20decided%20to%20follow%20his%20passion%20for%20tattooing%20and%20now%20he%20makes%20even%20more%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Daniel%20Sprague%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20who%20formerly%20worked%20at%20Google%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Austin.%20His%20employment%20has%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20text%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Google%20as%20a%20full%20life%20cycle%20recruiter%20for%20YouTube%20in%20September%202021%20in%20New%20York.%20When%20I%20was%20offered%20the%20role%2C%20I%20was%20hesitant%20at%20first%2C%20but%20looking%20at%20YouTube's%20culture%20I%20realized%20there's%20no%20way%20I%20wanted%20to%20pass%20up%20on%20that%20opportunity.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20role%20included%20both%20sourcing%20and%20recruiting%2C%20predominantly%20for%20product%20management%20roles%20at%20YouTube.%20I%20oversaw%20the%20entire%20candidate%20hiring%20process%20from%20reaching%20out%20to%20them%20all%20the%20way%20through%20to%20finalizing%20their%20offer.%20It%20was%20super%20exciting%20and%20I%20got%20to%20work%20with%20some%20intensely%20cool%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20changed%20in%20October%202022%20because%20there%20was%20a%20hiring%20freeze.%20I%20was%20moved%20over%20to%20recruiting%20at%20Google%20for%20optical%20engineering%20roles%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20as%20much%20fun%20there%20because%20the%20culture%20is%20different%20from%20some%20of%20the%20companies%20that%20have%20been%20acquired%20by%20Google%20like%20YouTube.%20At%20Google%2C%20they%20had%20definitely%20over-hired%20and%20there%20just%20wasn't%20enough%20work%20for%20everyone.%20A%20lot%20of%20positions%20were%20essentially%20doing%20the%20same%20thing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20are%20promoted%2C%20your%20role%20doesn't%20change%20very%20much%2C%20just%20the%20salary.%20You're%20progressing%20on%20paper%20but%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20a%20true%20progression%20outside%20of%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20was%20slated%20to%20be%20converted%20to%20a%20permanent%20employee%20from%20a%20contractor%2C%20the%20hiring%20freeze%20began%20and%20there%20were%20no%20available%20roles.%20I%20realized%20it%20would%20be%20truly%20hard%20to%20progress%20and%20find%20happiness%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20saw%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20because%20mass%20layoffs%20were%20happening%20everywhere%20and%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20speculation%20in%20the%20news%20about%20the%20same%20thing%20happening%20at%20Google.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20layoffs%20because%20as%20a%20contractor%20there%20aren't%20many%20benefits%20you%20can%20receive.%20All%20the%20permanent%20employees%20would%20get%20severance%20but%20as%20a%20contractor%2C%20it's%20just%20'goodbye.'%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20earning%20well%20over%20six-figures%20at%20Google%2C%20but%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20in%20December%202022%20to%20grow%20my%20tattoo%20business%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Feveronwardink%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEver%20Onward%20Ink%3C%2Fa%3E%20full-time.%20My%20income%20has%20now%20increased%20and%20I%20feel%20more%20comfortable%20in%20my%20day-to-day%20life.%20(BI%20was%20able%20to%20verify%20Sprague's%20income%20via%20a%20copy%20of%20his%20offer%20email%20from%20Google%20and%20his%20recent%20bank%20statements.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20spent%20my%20weekends%20tattooing%20whilst%20working%20at%20Google%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Sprague.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584213e1c5c7b8c9a0ad994%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESprague%20tattooing%20a%20client.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Sprague%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20drawing%20in%20high%20school%20and%20even%20won%20a%20few%20Scholastic%20awards%2C%20but%20I%20grew%20up%20thinking%20that%20art%20was%20not%20a%20way%20to%20make%20money.%20It%20was%20a%20good%20hobby%2C%20but%20I'd%20heard%20about%20the%20starving%20artist%20paradigm%20and%20it%20wasn't%20for%20me%20to%20be%20sitting%20there%20in%20art%20school%2C%20not%20really%20thinking%20about%20a%20future%20prospect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20college%2C%20I%20did%20do%20a%20few%20galleries%20and%20showcases%20where%20I%20made%20art%20specifically%20for%20the%20intent%20of%20having%20it%20collected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20introduced%20to%20tattooing%20by%20a%20friend%20a%20little%20later%20on.%20It%20seemed%20a%20little%20dangerous%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20hurt%20anyone%2C%20so%20I%20tried%20out%20tattooing%20on%20fake%20skin%20and%20it%20came%20out%20nice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20one%20of%20my%20friends%20asked%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20my%20first%20tattoo%20on%20them.%20I%20said%20no%20