re%20for%20carbon%20offsetting%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20industrial%20equipment%20pumps%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20as%20a%20by-product%20of%20energy%20production%2C%20vegetation%20sucks%20it%20out%20as%20fuel%20for%20its%20own%20cells.%20By%20encouraging%20more%20forest%20growth%2C%20polluters%20can%20in%20theory%20cancel%20out%20their%20environmental%20debts.%20In%20reality%2C%20such%20carbon%20offsetting%20is%20rife%20with%20questionable%20accounting%2C%20turning%20it%20into%20a%20tempting%20way%20to%20avoid%20the%20hard%20work%20of%20decarbonization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20a%20welter%20of%20scandals%20over%20the%20past%20year%20showing%20that%20offsetting%20projects%20often%20overstated%20their%20benefits%2C%20culminating%20in%20a%20peer-reviewed%20study%20finding%20some%2094%25%20of%20the%20credits%20analyzed%20may%20be%20bogus.%20That's%20prompted%20corporate%20backers%20in%20rich%20countries%20-%20including%20Shell%20Plc%2C%20Nestle%20SA%2C%20easyJet%20Plc%20and%20Fortescue%20Metals%20Group%20Ltd.%20-%20to%20pull%20out.%20It's%20not%20deterring%20oil%20producers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20early-stage%20agreements%20that%20cover%20a%20fifth%20of%20Zimbabwe's%20land%20mass%20and%2010%25%20of%20Liberia%2C%20Blue%20Carbon%20is%20starting%20to%20resemble%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarbon%20colonialist%2C%26quot%3B%20akin%20to%20mid-20th%20century%20imperialist%20oil%20majors%20such%20as%20Shell%20and%20BP%20Plc.%20This%20month%2C%20it%20used%20the%20COP28%20meeting%20in%20its%20hometown%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20recruit%20more%20governments.%20It's%20helping%20turn%20Dubai's%20oil%20wealth%20into%20a%20worryingly%20potent%20-%20and%20corrupting%20-%20tool%20of%20climate%20diplomacy%20soft%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarbon%20offsetting%20may%20be%20full%20of%20greenwashing%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20collapse%20in%202023.%20If%20anything%2C%20it's%20just%20getting%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrake%20In%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlenty%20of%20ink%20has%20been%20spilled%20about%20the%20travails%20of%20wind%20energy%20in%20Europe%2C%20where%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%20rising%20costs%20for%20materials%2C%20and%20supply-chain%20bottlenecks%20led%20to%20failed%20power%20auctions%20and%20plunging%20share%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar%20less%20attention%20has%20been%20paid%20to%20the%20growing%20evidence%20that%20India%20is%20failing%20to%20hit%20its%20ambitious%20targets%20for%20clean%20energy.%20That%20may%20have%20the%20bigger%20impact%20on%20global%20emissions%2C%20though.%20Despite%20some%20of%20the%20lowest-cost%20renewable%20power%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20annual%20connections%20are%20stuck%20around%2010GW%20to%2015GW%2C%20and%20solar%20connections%20in%20the%20nine%20months%20through%20September%20fell%2047%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20according%20to%20Mercom%20India%20Research%2C%20a%20consultancy.%20The%20country%20needs%20to%20be%20adding%20about%2040GW%20each%20year%20to%20hit%20its%20target%20of%20500GW%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELongstanding%20roadblocks%20caused%20by%20deficient%20grid%20infrastructure%20and%20land%20acquisition%2C%20plus%20the%20perennial%20financially%20distressed%20condition%20of%20state-owned%20electricity%20distribution%20companies%2C%20don't%20show%20much%20sign%20of%20being%20fixed%20any%20time%20soon.%20If%20the%20world%20is%20to%20prevent%20India's%20development%20putting%20further%20upward%20pressure%20on%20global%20emissions%2C%20the%20country%20badly%20needs%20to%20achieve%20its%20ambition%20to%20enjoy%20the%20world's%20first%20green%20industrial%20revolution.%20That's%20looking%20increasingly%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESinking%20Hopes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20think%20all%20the%20greenhouse%20gases%20spewed%20out%20by%20human%20society%20end%20up%20in%20the%20sky.%20Not%20quite.%20In%20fact%2C%20about%20three-fifths%20of%20the%20total%20is%20absorbed%20into%20oceans%2C%20soils%2C%20and%20plants.%20All%20the%20warming%20we%20worry%20about%20is%20being%20caused%20by%20the%20remainder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20terrestrial%20and%20oceanic%20carbon%20sinks%20are%20vast%20and%20little-understood%2C%20making%20every%20piece%20of%20emerging%20scientific%20research%20vital%20to%20the%20question%20of%20how%20much%20we%20can%20afford%20to%20emit%20without%20causing%20devastating%20warming.%20One%20prominent%202022%20paper%20in%20the%20scientific%20journal%20Nature%2C%20which%20found%20that%20the%20sinks%20appeared%20to%20be%20taking%20up%20all%20the%20carbon%20that%20human%20activity%20was%20emitting%2C%20was%20retracted%20in%20September%20after%20queries%20about%20the%20statistical%20techniques%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20few%20weeks%20earlier%2C%20the%20journal%20AGU%20Advances%20published%20further%20troubling%20news%20on%20the%20global%20carbon%20cycle.%20Force%20enough%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20a%20bottle%20of%20water%20with%20a%20soda%20siphon%2C%20and%20at%20some%20point%20the%20liquid%20will%20approach%20saturation.%20Something%20similar%20may%20be%20happening%20to%20the%20world's%20seas.%20Rising%20CO2%20concentration%20is%20making%20the%20oceans%20more%20acidic%2C%20and%20the%20way%20water%20circulates%20is%20changing%2C%20too.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20seas%20have%20been%20taking%20up%20a%20smaller%20share%20of%20our%20emissions%20with%20each%20passing%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20worrying%20sign.%20If%20the%20oceans%20stop%20working%20as%20carbon%20dumps%20-%20or%2C%20worse%20still%2C%20start%20pushing%20their%20dissolved%20CO2%20back%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20-%20even%20declining%20emissions%20from%20human%20activities%20might%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20halt%20the%20rise%20in%20global%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESilver%20Linings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sounds%20like%20an%20unmitigatedly%20depressing%20way%20to%20end%20the%20year%20-%20but%20there's%20been%20some%20good%20news%20as%20well%2C%20not%20all%20of%20it%20hitting%20the%20headlines.%20Tomorrow%20we'll%20look%20at%20three%20reasons%20to%20be%20cheerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(David%20Fickling%20is%20a%20Bloomberg%20Opinion%20columnist%20covering%20commodities%2C%20as%20well%20as%20industrial%20and%20consumer%20companies.%20He%20has%20been%20a%20reporter%20for%20Bloomberg%20News%2C%20Dow%20Jones%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%2C%20the%20Financial%20Times%20and%20the%20Guardian.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20The%20opinions%20expressed%20within%20this%20article%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%20The%20facts%20and%20opinions%20appearing%20in%20the%20article%20do%20not%20reflect%20the%20views%20of%20NDTV%20and%20NDTV%20does%20not%20assume%20any%20responsibility%20or%20liability%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703584620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fmmdr0658_bloomberg-making-waves_625x300_26_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-years-worst-climate-news-you-havent-heard-about-4745130%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20was%20a%20year%20when%20the%20world%20experienced%20its%20hottest%2012%20months%20on%20record.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-years-worst-climate-news-you-havent-heard-about-4745130%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AB%20on%20how%20Big%20B%20took%20adrenaline%20shots%2C%20did%20double%20shifts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703584310000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106291184%2Cimgsize-79376.cms