Mizoram%20-%20in%20November%20and%20December.%20This%20initiated%20a%20significant%20conversation%20around%20lowering%20the%20age%20limit%20for%20contesting%20polls.%20It%20is%20unlikely%20to%20happen%20soon%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2018%20May%201949%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%2C%20tasked%20with%20creating%20India's%20Constitution%2C%20debated%20the%20insertion%20of%20an%20Article%20that%20set%20guidelines%20such%20as%20the%20minimum%20age%20for%20a%20parliamentarian%20in%20India.%20The%20motion%20was%20to%20set%2025%20years%20as%20the%20minimum%20age%20to%20enter%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%2035%20years%20for%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDurgabai%20Deshmukh%2C%20a%20legendary%20freedom%20fighter%20who%20fought%20bravely%20for%20women's%20emancipation%2C%20moved%20an%20amendment%20to%20this%20motion%20and%20sought%20to%20reduce%20the%20minimum%20age%20to%20enter%20Rajya%20Sabha%20from%2035%20to%2030.%20She%20felt%20that%20with%20the%20dynamicity%20of%20a%20new%20nation%2C%20the%20youth%20were%20considerably%20aware%20of%20their%20democratic%20responsibilities.%20She%20argued%20that%20wisdom%20does%20not%20depend%20on%20age%20and%20that%20young%20people%20must%20be%20trained%20in%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20state.%20Socialist%20leader%20HV%20Kamath%2C%20speaking%20in%20favour%20of%20this%20amendment%2C%20cited%20William%20Pitt%2C%20who%20entered%20the%20UK%20parliament%20at%2021%20and%20became%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20the%20country%20at%2024.%20Kamath%20held%20that%20the%20minimum%20age%20should%20be%20uniformly%20reduced%20to%2021%20for%20either%20house%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDurgabai%20was%20seconded%20by%20eminent%20figures%20such%20as%20Shibban%20Lal%20Saxena%20(arrested%20for%20organising%20a%20protest%20in%20Kanpur%20against%20the%20Jallianwala%20Bagh%20massacre)%20and%20Tajamul%20Hussain%20(barrister%20and%20two-time%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP).%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20amendment%20was%20adopted%20and%20today%20it%20remains%20in%20our%20constitution%20as%20Article%2084%20and%20Article%20173.%20These%20Articles%20prescribe%2025%20and%2030%20years%20as%20the%20lower%20limit%20for%20the%20lower%20and%20upper%20houses%20at%20both%20the%20Centre%20and%20in%20state%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20second%20debate.%20It%20began%20more%20than%2013%20years%20ago%20when%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20(PIL)%20filed%20by%20one%20Kumar%20Gaurav%20surprised%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20comprising%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20KG%20Balakrishnan%20and%20Justices%20R%20V%20Raveendran%20and%20Deepak%20Verma.%20The%20PIL%20called%20for%20a%20change%20in%20the%20age%20limit%20for%20contesting%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20elections%20to%2021%20years%20from%20the%20stipulated%2025%20years%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20age%20of%20voting%20had%20been%20reduced%20from%2021%20to%2018%20years.%20The%20judges%20responded%20with%20the%20insight%20that%20experience%20in%20politics%20is%20a%20must%20before%20contesting%20elections.%20The%20counsel%20for%20Kumar%20Gaurav%20said%20it%20was%20the%20people's%20fundamental%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20profession%20and%20politics%20had%20become%20one.%20The%20counsel%20also%20said%20in%20many%20countries%20the%20age%20limit%20for%20people's%20representatives%20had%20been%20reduced%20to%2018%20years%20and%20that%20India%20should%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PIL%20was%20dismissed%2C%20but%20a%20parliamentary%20panel%20was%20asked%20to%20discuss%20lowering%20the%20minimum%20age%20for%20contesting%20an%20assembly%20election%20from%2025%20to%2018%20years.%20The%20panel%20said%20it%20would%20widen%20the%20viewpoints%20in%20policy%20debates%2C%20thus%20improving%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20presented%20a%20report%20on%20the%20aspects%20of%20the%20election%20process%20and%20reforms%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20The%20panel%2C%20chaired%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Sushil%20Kumar%2C%20also%20cautioned%20the%20government%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20on%20their%20proposal%20for%20a%20common%20electoral%20roll%20for%20parliamentary%2C%20assembly%20and%20local%20body%20elections.%20In%20summary%2C%20it%20suggested%20sticking%20to%20principles%20of%20federalism.%20The%20committee%20also%20recommended%20raising%20the%20punishment%20for%20a%20candidate%20filing%20a%20false%20affidavit%20from%20six%20months%20to%20up%20to%20two%20years%20and%20a%20fine%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20highlights%20the%20observation%20that%20reducing%20the%20minimum%20age%20requirement%20for%20elections%20will%20give%20young%20individuals%20equal%20opportunities%20to%20engage%20in%20democracy.%20This%20viewpoint%20is%20reinforced%20by%20a%20vast%20amount%20of%20evidence%2C%20such%20as%20global%20practices%2C%20the%20increasing%20political%20consciousness%20among%20young%20people%20and%20the%20advantages%20of%20youth%20representation.%20The%20report%20added%20that%20political%20parties%20had%20in%20the%20past%20favoured%20experienced%20candidates%20for%20public%20office%20while%20dismissing%20younger%20candidates%20as%20lacking%20in%20experience.%20This%20suggests%20that%20political%20competence%20comes%20with%20age%2C%20a%20notion%20that%20Plato%20argued%20for%20over%202%2C000%20years%20ago.%20However%2C%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20this%20belief%20is%20increasingly%20being%20considered%20outdated.%20Due%20to%20the%20expansion%20in%20education%2C%20globalisation%20and%20digitalisation%2C%20younger%20individuals%20are%20now%20more%20than%20capable%20of%20running%20for%20office%20in%20all%20countries.%20The%20committee%20raised%20its%20points%20on%20some%20solid%20logic.%20The%20committee%20said%20it%20was%20disconcerting%20that%2047%20per%20cent%20of%20MPs%20in%202019%20were%20over%2055%2C%20per%20PRS%20Legislative%20Research%2C%20while%20India's%20median%20age%20was%2027.9%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20note%20in%20this%20context%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20did%20not%20agree%20with%20the%20need%20to%20change%20the%20minimum%20age.%20The%20poll%20panel%20made%20it%20clear%20in%20its%20input%20to%20the%20committee%20that%20it%20had%20considered%20the%20issue%20and%20found%20it%20unrealistic%20to%20expect%2018-year-olds%20to%20%26quot%3Bpossess%20the%20necessary%20experience%20and%20maturity%20for%20these%20responsibilities%26quot%3B.%20The%20Election%20Commission's%20viewpoint%20was%20based%20on%20its%20belief%20that%2018-year-olds%20might%20not%20possess%20the%20necessary%20experience%20and%20maturity%20to%20shoulder%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20parliamentary%20and%20state%20legislative%20roles.%20The%20committee%20still%20argued%20it%20had%20been%20observed%20through%20surveys%2C%20which%20indicated%20that%20youth%20globally%20had%20significant%20political%20awareness%20and%20knowledge.%20It%20was%20evident%20through%20youth-led%20movements%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EFridays%20for%20Future%20and%20March%20for%20Our%20Lives%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20highlighting%20their%20capacity%20to%20rally%20and%20champion%20critical%20social%20and%20political%20concerns.%20Then%20the%20aim%20of%20providing%20young%20individuals%20equal%20opportunities%20to%20actively%20engage%20in%20democracy%20needs%20to%20be%20pursued.%20More%20importantly%2C%20young%20individuals%20can%20be%20reliable%20and%20responsible%20political%20participants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20present%20legal%20framework%2C%20a%20person%20must%20be%20at%20least%2025%20years%20old%20to%20contest%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20polls%2C%20and%20the%20minimum%20age%20for%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20council%20membership%20is%2030%20years.%20As%20things%20stand%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20called%20upon%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20the%20government%20to%20prioritise%20providing%20comprehensive%20civic%20education%20programs%20to%20equip%20young%20people%20with%20the%20knowledge%20and%20skills%20necessary%20for%20political%20engagement.%20The%20potential%20adoption%20of%20successful%20models%2C%20such%20as%20Finland's%20citizenship%20education%2C%20tailored%20to%20suit%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20is%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20clear.%20In%20today's%20globalised%20world%2C%20young%20men%20and%20women%20are%20aware%20of%20their%20rights%20and%20responsibilities%20and%20are%20vocal%20about%20all%20political%20issues.%20International%20movements%20like%20%3Cem%3EFridays%20for%20Future%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20advance%20climate%20change%20dialogue%20globally%20were%20started%20by%20young%20activists.%20So%20we%20must%20ask%20ourselves%3A%20Have%20we%20given%20our%20youth%20those%20very%20seats%20at%20the%20high%20table%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(V.%20VijayaSai%20Reddy%20is%20a%20Member%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20Chairman%2C%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Transport%2C%20Tourism%20and%20Culture)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703583240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-02%2Fjtvegvdo_election-2022-election-generic-evm-generic-ani-650_625x300_20_February_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-lowering-age-be-a-gamechanger-in-state-polls-4744960%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elections%20were%20held%20in%20five%20states%20-%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Telangana%20and%20Mizoram%20-%20in%20November%20and%20December.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-lowering-age-be-a-gamechanger-in-state-polls-4744960%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20the%20former%20Microsoft%20VP%20of%20HR.%20Here's%20what%20executive%20leadership%20really%20thinks%20about%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20layoffs%20are%20so%20common%20in%20Q1%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22200474299-001%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6585dcd0a79e5746976cd0eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22306%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChris%20Williams%20writes%20that%20executives%20are%20often%20thinking%20more%20long-term.%3Cp%3EMcMillan%20Digital%20Art%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChris%20Williams%20was%20the%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20is%20now%20a%20podcaster%2C%20consultant%2C%20and%20TikTok%20creator.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20writes%20that%20in%20the%20C-Suite%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20mood%20is%20not%20frantic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWilliams%20explains%20why%20layoffs%20are%20common%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20is%20a%20time%20for%20celebrations%20and%20family%20gatherings.%20In%20the%20working%20world%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20brings%20a%20push%20to%20the%20finish%20line%20%E2%80%94%20A%20chance%20to%20wrap%20things%20up%20for%20the%20year%20and%20to%20finish%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year-end%20also%20often%20brings%20holiday%20time%20off%2C%20a%20chance%20to%20get%20away%20from%20work%20and%20ponder.%20Even%20if%20it%20doesn't%20mark%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20calendar%20year%20affords%20time%20for%20reflection.%20A%20moment%20to%20review%20the%20year%20just%20past%20and%20to%20set%20resolutions%20for%20the%20year%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20reflections%20are%20different%20at%20the%20top%20than%20they%20are%20in%20most%20companies.%20As%20a%2040%2B%20year%20veteran%20of%20the%20corporate%20world%20and%20the%20former%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20I've%20seen%20that%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20falls%20differently%20in%20the%20C-Suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20those%20differences%20yield%20repercussions%20felt%20well%20into%20the%20new%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFinish%20the%20year%20strong%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20of%20the%20people%20in%20the%20company%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20is%20a%20time%20to%20finish%20the%20year%20strong.%20To%20meet%20major%20goals%20or%20wrap%20up%20projects%20neatly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20revenue-generation%20parts%20of%20the%20company%2C%20the%20year-end%20marks%20a%20crucial%20deadline.%20Hitting%20or%20missing%20targets%20can%20mean%20large%20differences%20in%20pay%20and%20promotion.%20This%20results%20in%20a%20flurry%20of%20activity%2C%20trying%20to%20close%20every%20possible%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20company%2C%20managers%20are%20looking%20to%20check%20off%20the%20list%20every%20possible%20win.%20Or%20to%20clear%20lingering%20projects%20setting%20the%20team%20up%20for%20a%20strong%20new%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20executive%20suite%2C%20the%20pace%20is%20often%20less%20frantic.%20Yes%2C%20targets%20and%20goals%20are%20important%2C%20their%20bonus%20is%20on%20the%20line%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20their%20time%20horizons%20are%20so%20long%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20same.%20They%20work%20quarters%2C%20years%2C%20even%20decades%20into%20the%20future.%20The%20December%20crunch%20just%20isn't%20meaningful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20the%20levers%20they%20maneuver%20are%20too%20large%20and%20sluggish.%20There's%20little%20they%20can%20change%20that%20will%20affect%20even%20this%20quarter%20let%20alone%20December.%20They%20can't%20start%20new%20projects%2C%20make%20new%20deals%2C%20change%20the%20organization%2C%20or%20close%20or%20open%20facilities%20fast%20enough%20to%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%20the%20C-Suite%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20mood%20is%20often%20one%20of%20acceptance%20of%20results%20they%20knew%20were%20coming%20a%20long%20time%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETime%20for%20a%20performance%20review%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20in%20the%20lower%20layers%20of%20the%20company%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20marks%20the%20arrival%20of%20performance%20reviews.%20The%20dreaded%20time%20where%20the%20prior%20year%20is%20rehashed%2C%20areas%20for%20improvement%20are%20detailed%2C%20vague%20goals%20are%20set%20for%20the%20future%2C%20and%20compensation%20is%20reevaluated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20makes%20for%20an%20uneasy%20year-end%20for%20many.%20They%20ruminate%20over%20mistakes%2C%20question%20their%20choices%2C%20and%20wallow%20in%20too%20much%20%26quot%3Bif%20only%26quot%3B.%20The%20result%20is%20a%20firm%20conviction%20to%20do%20better%2C%20with%20resolutions%20to%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20C-Suite%2C%20performance%20reviews%20fall%20differently.%20Though%20many%20get%20a%20similar%20form%20of%20review%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20company%2C%20the%20impact%20is%20far%20less.%20The%20top%20executive%20is%20reviewed%20by%20the%20board%2C%20and%20like%20most%20decisions%20made%20by%20committee%2C%20that%20review%20contains%20far%20fewer%20clear%20insights.%20And%20that%20review%20is%20highly%20focused%20on%20results%2C%20not%20behaviors%2C%20skills%2C%20or%20personal%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20implementation%20of%20performance%20reviews%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20is%20hampered%20by%20the%20compensation%20models%20up%20there.%20With%20income%20skewed%20heavily%20to%20equity%2C%20the%20only%20performance%20that%20truly%20matters%20is%20the%20stock%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20performance%20reviews%20that%20happen%20at%20the%20C-Suite%20level%20are%20less%20about%20the%20occupant%20of%20the%20job%2C%20and%20much%20more%20about%20the%20health%20of%20the%20business.%20Individual%20leadership%20performance%20is%20muddied%20with%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20team%20they%20lead.%20The%20action%20items%20that%20are%20set%20for%20the%20new%20year%20are%20about%20business%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20personal%20%E2%80%94%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%20the%20C-Suite%2C%20the%20performance%20reviews%20are%20still%20difficult%2C%20but%20rarely%20so%20personal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStart%20fresh%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20and%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20year%20offers%20a%20clear%20reset.%20It's%20a%20chance%20to%20shake%20bad%20habits%20and%20establish%20fresh%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20working%20world%20that%20means%20moving%20on%20from%20failing%20efforts%20and%20setting%20new%20targets.%20New%20Year's%20resolutions%20aren't%20just%20about%20weight%20loss.%20They%20can%20be%20about%20communication%20and%20time%20management%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20in%20the%20company%20often%20schedule%20new%20year%20kick%20off%20meetings.%20To%20start%20the%20year%20off%20right%2C%20to%20begin%20fresh.%20These%20are%20the%20result%20of%20their%20own%20reflections%20over%20the%20holidays%2C%20and%20their%20determination%20to%20set%20a%20strong%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20C-Suite%2C%20the%20same%20impulse%20is%20there%2C%20but%20here%20again%20their%20performance%20metrics%20and%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20levers%20they%20control%20change%20their%20actions.%20Rather%20than%20schedule%20a%20meeting%20or%20setting%20new%20targets%2C%20in%20the%20C-Suite%20the%20changes%20are%20often%20of%20vastly%20larger%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20why%20you%20see%20so%20many%20company%20reorganizations%20and%20layoffs%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20executives%20have%20had%20time%20to%20imagine%20a%20new%20future%2C%20and%20often%20that%20means%20a%20vastly%20different%20organization.%20Sometimes%20smaller%2C%20always%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20year%20is%20also%20a%20favorite%20time%20for%20the%20start%20of%20new%20initiatives.%20New%20projects%2C%20new%20businesses%2C%20or%20expansion%20into%20new%20markets.%20There's%20something%20about%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20that%20makes%20hope%20spring%20eternal.%20Maybe%20it's%20the%20eggnog%20around%20the%20fireplace%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20efforts%20will%20take%20time%20to%20bear%20fruit%2C%20and%20for%20the%20executive%20under%20financial%20pressure%2C%20they%20need%20to%20move%20faster%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThat's%20why%20layoffs%20are%20so%20common%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECutting%20headcount%20is%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20financial%20impacts%20a%20C-Suite%20executive%20has%20at%20their%20disposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20layoffs%20may%20have%20been%20pending%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20executive's%20mind%20for%20some%20time.%20But%20a%20layoff%20around%20the%20holidays%20is%20in%20such%20poor%20taste%20that%20most%20have%20been%20convinced%20by%20the%20HR%20team%20to%20delay%20it%20until%20the%20new%20year.%20The%20first%20quarter%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20C-Suite%20is%20concerned%20with%20the%20impacts%20they%20can%20have%2C%20and%20the%20changes%20they%20can%20make%20that%20will%20change%20the%20financials%20of%20the%20company.%20At%20the%20scales%20of%20time%20and%20organization%20they%20work%2C%20those%20changes%20reach%20far%20into%20the%20future%2C%20and%20deep%20into%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20come%20back%20in%20the%20new%20year%2C%20take%20solace%20in%20one%20thought.%20While%20you%20are%20worrying%20over%20your%20pending%20performance%20review%2C%20the%20C-Suite%20is%20worried%20about%20theirs%20too.%20But%20theirs%20is%20given%20largely%20by%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bareas%20for%20improvement%26quot%3B%20are%20usually%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clwill.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EChris%20Williams%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20former%20VP%20of%20