eb-stories%2Fananya-panday-looks-like-a-vision-in-a-dreamy-white-pearl-lehenga%2Fphotostory%2F106223557.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20Have%20Covid.%20Here's%20How%20Likely%20I%20Am%20To%20Get%20Long%20Covid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEG.5%20or%20the%20Eris%20COVID%20variant%20is%20dominant%20in%20parts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.nsw.gov.au%2FInfectious%2Fcovid-19%2FDocuments%2Frespiratory-surveillance-20231202.pdf%5C%22%3EAustralia%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Eris%2C%20along%20with%20other%20circulating%20strains%2C%20are%20descendants%20of%20Omicron.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20strains%20appear%20less%20severe%20than%20the%20original%20Alpha%20and%20Delta%20variants%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20long%20COVID%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20the%20latest%20data%20say%20about%20the%20chance%20of%20long%20COVID%3F%20What%20symptoms%20should%20you%20look%20out%20for%3F%20And%20what%20can%20be%20done%20to%20support%20people%20with%20long%20COVID%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhen%20COVID%20becomes%20%E2%80%98long%20COVID'%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%2C%20long%20COVID%20means%20not%20getting%20better%20after%20a%20COVID%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications-detail-redirect%2FWHO-2019-nCoV-Post_COVID-19_condition-Clinical_case_definition-2021.1%5C%22%3Edefines%20long%20COVID%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20continuing%20or%20new%20symptoms%20at%20least%20three%20months%20from%20the%20start%20of%20a%20COVID%20infection%20that%20last%20at%20least%20two%20months%20and%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20an%20alternative%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10654-022-00962-6%5C%22%3Ecommon%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20fatigue%2C%20brain%20fog%2C%20breathlessness%2C%20headaches%20and%20abdominal%20pain.%20But%20people%20with%20long%20COVID%20can%20experience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1684118222001864%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3Ea%20wide%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20problems%20including%20cardiovascular%20issues%2C%20mental%20health%20problems%20such%20as%20depression%20and%20anxiety%2C%20insomnia%2C%20muscle%20and%20joint%20pain%2C%20and%20gastrointestinal%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20common%20is%20long%20COVID%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralian%20data%20on%20long%20COVID%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2023%2F218%2F10%2Flong-covid-australia-achieving-equitable-access-supportive-health-care%5C%22%3Eremains%20limited%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww150.statcan.gc.ca%2Fn1%2Fpub%2F75-006-x%2F2023001%2Farticle%2F00015-eng.htm%5C%22%3Einternational%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20estimates%20of%20its%20prevalence%20have%20varied.%20A%20report%20from%20Australia's%20parliamentary%20inquiry%20into%20long%20COVID%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fparlinfo.aph.gov.au%2FparlInfo%2Fdownload%2Fcommittees%2Freportrep%2FRB000006%2Ftoc_pdf%2FSickandtiredCastingalongshadow.pdf%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20suggested%202%25-20%25%20of%20people%20may%20develop%20long%20COVID%20following%20an%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20Australian%20study%20conducted%20when%20vaccines%20were%20widely%20available%20indicates%20earlier%20Omicron%20variants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.3390%2Fijerph20186756%5C%22%3Esaw%2010%25%20of%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20caught%20COVID%20develop%20long%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20recent%20study%2C%20yet%20to%20be%20peer-reviewed%2C%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medrxiv.org%2Fcontent%2F10.1101%2F2023.08.06.23293706v1%5C%22%3E18.2%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20those%20infected%20went%20on%20to%20have%20long%20COVID.%20The%20wide-ranging%20estimates%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20because%20of%20different%20COVID%20variants%2C%20differences%20in%20vaccination%2C%20and%20different%20long%20COVID%20definitions%20and%20assessment%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20is%20lower%20in%20children.%20One%20Australian%20study%20indicated%20persistent%20symptoms%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanchi%2Farticle%2FPIIS2352-4642(21)00124-3%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E8%25%20of%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20had%20COVID%20in%202020%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medrxiv.org%2Fcontent%2F10.1101%2F2023.03.14.23287239v1%5C%22%3Epreliminary%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20points%20to%20a%20slightly%20lower%20risk%20among%20children%20infected%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20research%20is%20needed%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20virus%20continues%20to%20evolve.%20This%20can%20be%20complicated%20because%20typical%20long%20COVID%20symptoms%20are%20common%20to%20many%20other%20health%20problems.%20As%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20more%20research%20is%20now%20underway%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apprise.org.au%2Fbroad-research-area%2Finsights-into-long-covid%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20determine%20the%20accurate%20prevalence%20of%20the%20condition%20using%20a%20definition%20and%20methods%20that%20carefully%20exclude%20other%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20research%20on%20long%20COVID%20risk%20factors%20with%20new%20variants%20is%20ongoing%2C%20we%20expect%20being%20female%2C%20having%20more%20severe%20initial%20disease%20and%20having%20other%20health%20conditions%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1001%2Fjamainternmed.2023.0750%5C%22%3Eincrease%20a%20person's%20chance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20getting%20long%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20different%20this%20time%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20COVID%20vaccines%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F1660-4601%2F19%2F19%2F12422%5C%22%3Eprotection%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20long%20COVID.%20As%20well%20as%20vaccinations%2C%20immunity%20from%20previous%20COVID%20infections%20and%20antiviral%20treatments%20are%20contributing%20to%20less%20severe%20COVID%20and%20potentially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcould-antivirals-reduce-your-risk-of-long-covid-where-the-research-is-up-to-on-prevention-and-treatment-216529%5C%22%3Eless%20long%20COVID%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20we%20saw%20earlier%20in%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20Omicron%20waves%20may%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smh.com.au%2Fnational%2Fnewer-virus-strains-less-likely-to-cause-long-covid-20231123-p5emag.html%5C%22%3Efewer%20cases%20of%20long%20COVID%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20earlier%20Alpha%20and%20Delta%20variants%2C%20because%20so%20many%20Australians%20are%20contracting%20COVID%2C%20this%20will%20still%20result%20in%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20with%20long%20COVID.%20And%20each%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww150.statcan.gc.ca%2Fn1%2Fpub%2F75-006-x%2F2023001%2Farticle%2F00015-eng.htm%5C%22%3Erepeat%20infection%3C%2Fa%3E%20presents%20a%20new%20risk%20of%20prolonged%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ELong%20COVID%20can%20affect%20all%20aspects%20of%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20COVID%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1093%2Fije%2Fdyad033%5C%22%3Eimpact%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20person's%20life%20in%20many%20ways.%20Fatigue%20following%20exertion%2C%20brain%20fog%20and%20other%20symptoms%20can%20reduce%20capacity%20to%20perform%20tasks%20such%20as%20concentrating%20at%20a%20computer%2C%20manual%20labour%2C%20and%20even%20normal%20household%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20with%20long%20COVID%20submitted%20evidence%20to%20the%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aph.gov.au%2FParliamentary_Business%2FCommittees%2FHouse%2FHealth_Aged_Care_and_Sport%2FLongandrepeatedCOVID%2FReport%2FChapter_4_-_Lived_experiences_of_long_COVID%5C%22%3Eparliamentary%20inquiry%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20were%20unsupported%2C%20stigmatised%2C%20isolated%2C%20and%20not%20taken%20seriously%20by%20health%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvidence%20suggests%20many%20symptoms%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanepe%2Farticle%2FPIIS2666-77622200250-2%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Ewill%20improve%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20most%20people%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Feclinm%2Farticle%2FPIIS2589-5370(23)00138-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E12%20to%2018%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20although%20recovery%20time%20can%20differ%20between%20symptoms.%20Some%2C%20including%20gastrointestinal%20and%20respiratory%20symptoms%2C%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41579-022-00846-2%5C%22%3Eresolve%20sooner%20than%20others%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20cognitive%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EI%20think%20I%20have%20long%20COVID%2C%20what%20can%20I%20expect%20from%20my%20doctor%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20COVID%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20challenge%20Australia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdx.doi.org%2F10.5694%2Fmja2.51950%5C%22%3Ehealth%20system%20finds%20most%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E.%20GPs%20are%20stretched%20and%20the%20small%20number%20of%20specialist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2023-12-12%2Flong-covid-clinics-are-closing-as-us-clinic-expands%2F103186272%5C%22%3Elong%20COVID%20clinics%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20struggling%20to%20maintain%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20has%20trailed%20behind%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20Europe%20in%20rolling%20out%20care%20for%20long%20COVID%2C%20and%20in%20collecting%20data%20on%20the%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20support%20for%20long%20COVID%20in%20Australia%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.3389%2Fphrs.2023.1606084%5C%22%3Ehard%20to%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20expensive%20and%20patchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20consensus%20on%20what%20constitutes%20good%20care.%20Clinicians%20seeing%20patients%20with%20possible%20long%20COVID%20should%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Evalidate%20the%20person's%20experience%20of%20symptoms%20and%20the%20impact%20their%20symptoms%20are%20having%20on%20their%20functioning%2C%20particularly%20when%20the%20cause%20is%20not%20clear%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ediagnose%20and%20treat%20any%20other%20health%20conditions%20that%20are%20part%20of%20the%20picture%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Esupport%20people%20to%20minimise%20the%20impairment%20their%20symptoms%20cause%20by%20pacing%20of%20physical%20and%20cognitive%20activities.%20Importantly%2C%20this%20doesn't%20involve%20pushing%20through%20fatigue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20steps%20are%20not%20a%20cure%20but%20they%20may%20improve%20a%20person's%20ability%20to%20function%20in%20their%20day-to-day%20life%2C%20at%20work%20and%20to%20fulfil%20their%20caring%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWe%20still%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20reducing%20COVID%20transmission%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20prevent%20long%20COVID%20is%20to%20avoid%20contracting%20%E2%80%93%20and%20spreading%20%E2%80%93%20COVID.%20This%20means%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Egetting%20vaccinated%20or%20boosted%2C%20if%20you're%20eligible%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Estaying%20home%20if%20you%20feel%20unwell%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ewearing%20a%20mask%20to%20protect%20yourself%20and%20vulnerable%20community%20members%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Etesting%20for%20COVID%20if%20you%20have%20symptoms%20and%20if%20you%20test%20positive%2C%20taking%20antivirals%20(if%20eligible)%20and%20isolating%20until%20your%20symptoms%20resolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20COVID%20is%20not%20going%20away%2C%20but%20we%20all%20have%20a%20role%20to%20play%20in%20preventing%20and%20respondin