%22Russia%3A%20Alexei%20Navalny%20Located%20in%20Siberia%20Prison%2C%20Allies%20Say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F26105251%2Fimage-1-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdoing%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20his%20spokeswoman%20Kira%20Yarmysh%20said%20on%20Monday%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20Russian%20opposition%20figure%20had%20been%20located%20in%20a%20penal%20colony%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20far%20north%2C%20in%20the%20Yamalo-Nenets%20region%20of%20western%20Siberia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20critic%20has%20been%20missing%20for%20weeks%2C%20with%20many%20fearing%20for%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20found%20Alexey%20Navalny.%20He%20is%20now%20in%20IK-3%20settlement%20of%20Kharp%20in%20the%20Yamal-Nenets%20Autonomous%20District%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yarmysh%20wrote%20on%20social%20media%2C%20using%20alternative%20spellings%20for%20Navalny%20and%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20lawyer%20visited%20him%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%E2%80%99s%20whereabouts%20had%20been%20unknown%20since%20early%20December%2C%20with%20friends%20and%20family%20unable%20to%20reach%20him%2C%20and%20court%20appointments%20in%20the%20various%20cases%20against%20him%20had%20been%20delayed%20without%20authorities%20providing%20reasons%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20had%20prompted%20concern%20among%20his%20supporters%20and%20international%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConditions%20%E2%80%98brutal%E2%80%99%20in%20Polar%20Wolf%20camp%2C%20Navalny%20colleague%20says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20found%20Alexei!%E2%80%9D%20the%20manager%20of%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation%20organisation%2C%20Ivan%20Zhdanov%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20IK-3%20facility%20was%20nicknamed%20the%20%E2%80%9CPolar%20Wolf%E2%80%9D%20prison%20camp%20and%20that%20it%20was%20among%20the%20most%20remote%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20conditions%20there%20are%20brutal%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20According%20to%20Zhdanov%2C%20there%20is%20permafrost%20at%20the%20camp%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20reach%20and%20no%20letters%20are%20delivered%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharp%20is%20a%20remote%20town%20of%20around%206%2C500%20people%2C%20according%20to%20a%202010%20census%2C%20in%20the%20Ural%20mountains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZhdanov%20said%20the%20move%20should%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20He%20has%20repeatedly%20accused%20the%20Kremlin%20of%20trying%20to%20isolate%20Navalny%20ahead%20of%20the%20presidential%20election%20on%20March%2017%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fvladimir-putin%2Ft-17449200%5C%22%3EVladimir%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20expected%20to%20win%20another%20term.%20This%20would%20be%20his%20fifth%20as%20president%20with%20a%20period%20as%20prime%20minister%20between%202008%20and%202012.%20Term%20limit%20rules%20have%20been%20abolished%20in%20Russia%20with%20relative%20ease%20since%20Putin%20first%20took%20power%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20was%20previously%20being%20held%20in%20the%20IK-6%20prison%20facility%2C%20a%20comparatively%20short%20distance%20southeast%20of%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20%E2%80%98deeply%20concerned%E2%80%99%20over%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20condemned%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20detention%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunjust%E2%80%9D%20and%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20conditions%20in%20the%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20remain%20deeply%20concerned%20for%20Mr.%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20wellbeing%20and%20the%20conditions%20of%20his%20unjust%20detention%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20while%20adding%20that%20the%20State%20Department%20welcomes%20reports%20that%20he%20had%20been%20located.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWashington%20condemned%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmalicious%20targeting%E2%80%9D%20of%20Navalny%20and%20called%20for%20his%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20release%2C%20without%20conditions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20call%20on%20the%20Russian%20government%20to%20end%20its%20escalating%20repression%20of%20independent%20voices%20in%20Russia%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArrested%20in%202021%20after%20recovery%20from%202020%20poisoning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%2C%2047%2C%20made%20a%20name%20for%20himself%20by%20publicly%20calling%20out%20corruption%20at%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20and%20first%20made%20a%20run%20to%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmoscow%2Ft-19038132%5C%22%3EMoscow%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98s%20mayor%20in%202013.%20He%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation%2C%20known%20in%20Russia%20as%20the%20FBK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20faced%20repeated%20arrests%2C%20physical%20attacks%2C%20and%20various%20investigations%20and%20criminal%20proceedings%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnavalnys-latest-conviction-purely-political-allies-say%2Fa-66430050%5C%22%3Ehe%20described%20as%20politically%20motivated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20during%20his%20earlier%20years%20of%20political%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%20he%20survived%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frussia-alexei-navalnys-german-doctors-detail-poison-treatment%2Fa-56045644%5C%22%3EGerman%20doctors%20said%20was%20a%20case%20of%20attempted%20poisoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20a%20Soviet-era%20nerve%20agent%2C%20Novichok.%20Comatose%2C%20he%20was%20flown%20to%20Germany%20for%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Russian%20officials%20then%20warned%20that%20his%20convalescence%20in%20Germany%20violated%20the%20terms%20of%20his%20probation%20for%20a%20prior%20conviction.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Falexei-n