-police-station-on-dec-26-2824801%5C%22%3Emedia%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Beniwal%E2%80%99s%20complaints%20from%20December%202%20had%20accused%20the%20DVAC%20team%20of%20accessing%20sensitive%20case%20records%2C%20information%20and%20internal%20documents%20of%20the%20ED%20related%20to%20other%20cases%20which%20have%20no%20link%20with%20the%20alleged%20search%20case%2C%20and%20ransacking%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20entire%20office%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Police%20officers%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20received%20no%20such%20complaint%20from%20the%20ED%20on%20that%20date.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20December%2016%2C%202023%2C%20a%20reminder%20letter%20requesting%20action%20was%20received%20by%20the%20DGP%E2%80%99s%20office%20wherein%20the%20original%20complaint%20was%20enclosed.%20The%20DGP%20forwarded%20the%20reminder%20enclosed%20with%20the%20original%20complaint%20to%20the%20Madurai%20Police%20Commissioner%20to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20inquiry%20and%20send%20a%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20part%20of%20the%20inquiry%2C%20the%20Madurai%20Police%20Commissioner%20sent%20a%20letter%20calling%20the%20ED%20officials%20to%20give%20evidence%20to%20substantiate%20their%20allegations.%20But%20they%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20letter%20and%20insisted%20that%20the%20same%20be%20sent%20by%20post.%20We%20then%20sent%20the%20letter%20by%20registered%20post%E2%80%A6%20there%20is%20no%20response%20yet.%20They%20have%20not%20turned%20up%20for%20the%20inquiry%20so%20far%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20not%20correct%20to%20say%20that%20no%20action%20was%20taken%20on%20ED%E2%80%99s%20complaint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703568494000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovern