3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F24075850%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-23-at-12.13.33-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20depressing%20afternoon%2C%20as%20late%20afternoons%20in%20early%20November%20tend%20to%20be%20now.%20The%20air%20was%20sticky%20and%20the%20light%20was%20grey.%20%E2%80%9CNovember%20in%20Delhi%20used%20to%20be%20beautiful%2C%20and%20now%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20people%20would%20say%20to%20each%20other%2C%20sniffling%20and%20coughing%2C%20and%20shaking%20their%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20like%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jamal%20said%20to%20his%20companion%2C%20as%20he%20took%20one%20last%20drag%20at%20his%20cigarette.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20nothing%20like%20Gaza%2C%20Jamal%20bhai%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Habib.%20%E2%80%9CYou%2C%20of%20all%20people%2C%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20trivialising%20the%20tragedy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJamal%20and%20Habib%20were%20standing%20in%20a%20far%20corner%20at%20the%20back%20of%20the%20Press%20Club%20courtyard%2C%20watching%20the%20speakers%20at%20the%20Palestine%20protest.%20There%20were%20many%20empty%20chairs%2C%20but%20it%20was%20quiet%20at%20the%20back%2C%20where%20Jamal%20could%20smoke%20and%20have%20a%20parallel%20discussion%20on%20the%20event.%20They%20were%20there%20more%20in%20solidarity%2C%20less%20to%20actually%20listen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLook%20at%20the%20turn%20out!%20Nobody%20cares%20anymore%2C%20yaar.%20The%20same%2020%20people%20at%20every%20protest!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20are%20scared%20to%20come%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20becoming%20like%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20surveillance%2C%20jail%2C%20the%20average%20person%20overjoyed%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20Muslims%20being%20put%20in%20their%20place.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYes%20but%20Gaza%20is%20of%20a%20different%20order%2C%20Jamal%20bhai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20men%20in%20servers%E2%80%99%20white%20uniforms%20carried%20out%20a%20rather%20modest%20steel%20urn%20and%20some%20paper%20cups%20and%20placed%20them%20on%20a%20side%20table%20near%20the%20entrance%2C%20across%20the%20breadth%20of%20the%20courtyard%20from%20where%20they%20had%20been%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20look%20at%20the%20amount%20of%20tea!%20It%20becomes%20less%20and%20less%20each%20time.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20they%20ever%20have%20enough%20tea%20for%20everyone%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20like%20the%20place%20is%20teeming%20with%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20observed%20the%20steel%20container%20at%20the%20entrance%2C%20a%20woman%20slipped%20into%20the%20courtyard%20and%20into%20their%20line%20of%20vision.%20She%20surveyed%20the%20scene%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20a%20late%20entrant%2C%20and%20glancing%20hurriedly%20in%20all%20directions%20before%20she%20found%20her%20appropriate%20mark%20and%20started%20to%20stare%20at%20the%20podium%20in%20feigned%20focus.%20She%20also%20smiled%20distractedly%20at%20the%20two%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWakil%20saheb%20ma%E2%80%99am%20is%20here.%20We%20should%20discuss%20with%20her%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Habib.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20vaguely%20recognised%20the%20two%20men%20but%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20remember%20their%20names.%20She%20had%20always%20been%20very%20bad%20with%20names%2C%20and%20with%20faces.%20They%20were%20journalists%20probably%2C%20or%20students%2C%20or%20activists.%20She%20had%20seen%20them%20at%20protests%20before%2C%20and%20they%20had%20likely%20either%20spoken%20of%20disappointing%20judgments%2C%20or%20of%20the%20viability%20of%20going%20to%20court%20to%20fight%20for%20more%20freedoms.%20Thankfully%20she%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20expected%20to%20make%20conversation%20while%20the%20speeches%20were%20still%20on%3B%20perhaps%20she%E2%80%99d%20remember%20who%20they%20were%20by%20the%20time%20the%20programme%20ends.%20Tara%20was%20very%20good%20at%20not%20letting%20people%20guess%20that%20she%20had%20no%20idea%20who%20they%20were.%20She%20only%20had%20to%20be%20alert%20to%20clues%20during%20conversation%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20first%20focused%20on%20the%20speakers%2C%20and%20then%20on%20the%20steel%20urn.%20She%20poured%20herself%20some%20tea.%20The%20paper%20cup%20was%20tiny.%20%E2%80%98Could%20it%20be%20any%20smaller%3F%E2%80%99%20she%20thought%20irritably.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20had%20been%20delayed%20in%20court%20today.%20She%20had%20gone%20to%20Patiala%20House%20to%20oppose%20extended%20remand%20for%20an%20accused%2C%20and%20had%20delivered%20an%20impassioned%20speech%20on%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20liberty%2C%20and%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20custodial%20interrogations%20were%20bad%20in%20civil%20rights%20jurisprudence.%20The%20public%20prosecutor%20had%20smirked%2C%20the%20judge%20had%20looked%20bemused%2C%20then%20bored.%20He%20had%20abruptly%20asked%20if%20the%20affidavit%20had%20been%20duly%20signed%20by%20the%20pairvikar.%20Tara%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20sure%2C%20so%20her%20junior%20had%20had%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhere%20is%20the%20welfare%20stamp%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20judge%20asked%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20had%20turned%20to%20look%20helplessly%20at%20her%20junior.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20judge%20had%20looked%20at%20Tara%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMadam%20have%20you%20seen%20the%20case%20law%20on%20this%20question%3F%20We%20are%20governed%20by%20%3Cem%3ESurendar%20Gadling%3C%2Fem%3E!%20Application%20rejected.%20Next%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20left%20the%20court%2C%20a%20kindly%20old%20advocate%20stopped%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMadam%2C%20you%20are%20a%20constitutional%20lawyer.%20Here%2C%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20%3Cem%3Ezameeni%20bahas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Next%20time%20you%20check%20what%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20on%20the%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20was%20thinking%20that%20she%20must%20find%20out%20about%20welfare%20stamps%20for%20the%20future%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%20she%20should%20file%20a%20comprehensive%20challenge%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20practice%20of%20easy%20custodial%20remand%2C%20when%20she%20realised%20the%20programme%20had%20concluded.%20The%20two%20men%20were%20now%20standing%20next%20to%20her%20and%20smiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHullo!%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20cheerily.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20have%20both%20of%20you%20been%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20well%2C%20Ma%E2%80%99am.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGood%20event!%20Although%20I%20was%20expecting%20more%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20are%20scared%2C%20Ma%E2%80%99am.%20I%20was%20just%20saying%20to%20Habibi.%20They%20impose%20Section%20144%20restrictions%20before%20protests%2C%20disallow%20permissions%2C%20so%20many%20arrests.%20Can%20we%20not%20challenge%20it%2C%20Ma%E2%80%99am%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHave%20you%20been%20writing%20about%20it%2C%20Habibi%3F%E2%80%9D%20Tara%20looked%20at%20the%20young%20man%20who%20was%20apparently%20Habibi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabib%20looked%20a%20little%20surprised.%20Only%20his%20closest%20friends%20and%20family%20called%20him%20Habibi.%20%E2%80%9CNo%20Ma%E2%80%99am%2C%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20written.%20Where%20will%20I%20write%3F%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20becoming%20a%20serious%20issue%20Ma%E2%80%99am.%20We%20are%20not%20allowed%20any%20space%20to%20do%20anything.%20We%20had%20student%20union%20elections%20at%20the%20University%20and%20there%20was%20permanent%20curfew%20imposed%20on%20gatherings.%20We%20could%20do%20nothing.%20Jamal%20bhai%20is%20talking%20of%20the%20Jantar%20Mantar%20area%2C%20but%20even%20on%20campuses%20there%20is%20permanent%20curfew.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20a%20journalist%2C%20a%20student!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20are%20your%20exams%3F%E2%80%9D%20Tara%20asked%20with%20more%20confidence%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99ll%20be%20writing%20competitive%20exams%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20Ma%E2%80%99am%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habib%20said.%20Jamal%20shrugged%20noncommittally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWell%20then%2C%20Habibi%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20think%20of%20a%20petition%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20their%20goodbyes%2C%20and%20as%20Tara%20moved%20away%2C%20Jamal%20lunged%20at%20the%20urn%2C%20tilting%20it%20forward%20till%20it%20was%20level%20with%20the%20table.%20There%20was%20not%20even%20the%20thinnest%20stream%20of%20tea%20left.%20%E2%80%9CSee!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDoesn%E2%80%99t%20matter%2C%20Jamal%20bhai.%20We%20are%20not%20here%20to%20have%20tea.%20Come%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20go%20outside%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Ererhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20parking%20lot.%20He%20has%20the%20best%20tea%20and%20the%20best%20gossip.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20never%20going%20there.%20Students%20hang%20around%20having%20chai%20and%20mathri%20and%20the%20moment%20someone%20senior%20arrives%20they%20all%20conveniently%20leave.%20Last%20time%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20300%20rupees.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJamal%20lit%20another%20cigarette%20as%20they%20stepped%20out%20of%20the%20Press%20Club.%20Just%20at%20the%20entrance%2C%20a%20posse%20of%20policemen%20sat%20on%20plastic%20chairs%2C%20sipping%20tea%2C%20scrolling%20through%20their%20mobile%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20organisers%20are%20serving%20them%20tea%2C%20but%20not%20us!%E2%80%9D%20even%20Habibi%20was%20offended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHave%20you%20taken%20down%20all%20the%20attendees%20names%3F%E2%80%9D%20Jamal%20called%20out%20to%20the%20policemen%20provocatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EASI%20Achche%20Lal%20looked%20up%20and%20sighed.%20The%20intemperance%20of%20youth%2C%20he%20thought%20to%20himself.%20He%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20engage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAren%E2%80%99t%20you%20ashamed%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20this%20was%20a%20bit%20much.%20Achche%20Lal%20leapt%20to%20his%20feet%3A%20%E2%80%9CAren%E2%80%99t%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E%20ashamed%3F%20Going%20from%20one%20protest%20to%20another%20%E2%80%93%20not%20doing%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20honest%20work.%20Andolan%20jeevi%2C%20activist.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20students.%20I%20am%20preparing%20for%20my%20UPSC%20exams%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habib%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSerious%20students%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20all%20this.%20You%20should%20sit%20at%20home%20and%20prepare.%20And%20as%20for%20him%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20I%20know%3F%20Even%20he%20started%20off%20claiming%20he%20was%20preparing%20for%20competition.%20Now%20look%20at%20him%20%E2%80%93%20all%20age%20limits%20have%20passed.%20Wastrel%2C%20lives%20off%20his%20poor%20retired%20father.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20light%20had%20turned%20even%20darker.%20Jamal%20felt%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20breathe.%20%E2%80%9CIs%20Umar%20Khalid%20a%20wastrel%3F%20Every%20day%20there%20are%20injustices%20meted%20out.%20Nobody%20speaks%20up.%20Some%20of%20us%20have%20to%20protest.%20They%20said%20just%20now%20that%20we%20are%20the%20real%20patriots%2C%20we%20are%20the%20last%20line%20of%20defence%20for%20this%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstable%20Awdhesh%20Rana%2C%20tall%20and%20strapping%20got%20up%20from%20his%20chair%2C%20and%20swung%20his%20lathi%20at%20the%20two%20men.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20want%20to%20be%20Umar%20Khalid%3F%20I%E2%80%99ll%20show%20you%20Umar%20Khalid.%20Not%20only%20is%20he%20a%20wastrel%2C%20he%20is%20Jihadi.%20Terrorists%2C%20leeches%20all!%20I%E2%80%99ll%20book%20you%20under%20UAPA%20just%20now%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20As%20profanities%20flew%20from%20Constable%20Rana%E2%80%99s%20mouth%2C%20Habib%20felt%20a%20sharp%20stinging%20slap%20on%20his%20face.%20His%20eyes%20welled%20up.%20Jamal%E2%80%99s%20face%20was%20red.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchche%20Lal%20was%20shouting%20in%20anger%2C%20%E2%80%9CGet%20arrested%20and%20send%20your%20parents%20crying%20to%20me%20for%20help.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Press%20Club%20servers%20rushed%20out%20and%20intervened.%20%E2%80%9CSecretary%20saheb%20is%20calling%20both%20of%20you%20inside.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJamal%20and%20Habib%20were%20met%20with%20very%20grim%20faces%20inside.%20The%20secretary%20was%20livid%20at%20the%20organisers%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20how%20difficult%20it%20is%20to%20find%20places%20for%20such%20events.%20Gandhi%20Foundation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20give%20space%3B%20Jantar-Mantar%20is%20out%20of%20bounds.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20spaces%20left%2C%20and%20then%20these%20people%20create%20a%20tamasha.%20Why%20do%20you%20call%20such%20people%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organisers%20glowered.%20Jamal%20and%20Habib%20looked%20down%20at%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20moved%20forward%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20quite%20unnecessary%2C%20Jamal%20and%20Habibi.%20Pointless.%20You%E2%80%99d%20get%20booked%20under%20the%20UAPA%20for%20assaulting%20police%20officers%20and%20then%20stay%20inside%20for%20months.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20hit%20Habibi.%20He%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20even%20said%20anything%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20must%20know%20that%20that%20is%20exactly%20how%20it%20works.%20They%20always%20pick%20on%20innocent%20bystanders.%20Wasn%E2%80%99t%20that%20your%20point%20today%20at%20the%20protest%20about%20the%20assault%20on%20Gaza%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJamal%20bhai%20has%20sugar.%20When%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20eat%20for%20too%20long%20he%20gets%20angry%2C%20suddenly%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habib%20said%20softly%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20go%20and%20feed%20him.%20Take%20him%20away%20from%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20organisers%20disapprovingly%2C%20as%20the%20more%20senior%20lot%20requested%20Tara%20to%20come%20out%20with%20them%20to%20apologise%20to%20Achche%20Lal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20did%20it%20all%20start%3F%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Tara%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20said%20students%20should%20not%20be%20wasting%20their%20time%20on%20protests.%20Everyone%20should%20just%20study%2C%20or%20work%2C%20and%20not%20ask%20for%20any%20accountability.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWell%20in%20some%20countries%2C%20working%20unions%20protest%20collectively.%20They%20refuse%20to%20work%20in%20the%20face%20of%20gross%20injustice.%20Dockworkers%20in%20Spain%20refused%20to%20work%2C%20to%20load%20ships%20carrying%20arms%20to%20Israel.%20But%20when%20there%20is%20no%20collective%20responsibility%2C%20then%20the%20few%20who%20refuse%20to%20work%20are%20considered%20freeloaders.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20that%20is%20fine%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20time%20and%20place%20for%20such%20nuanced%20discussions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20won%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything.%20He%20is%20my%20uncle%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jamal%20said%20suddenly.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20domestic%20fight.%E2%80%9D%20Everyone%20turned%20to%20look%20at%20him%20in%20surprise.%20Tara%20felt%20relieved%20she%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20mediate%20with%20the%20police%20on%20his%20behalf.%20She%20felt%20that%20she%20had%20made%20some%20wise%20arguments%20before%20these%20men%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20just%20go%20home%20without%20once%20again%20feeling%20ineffective%20and%20dispirited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLeave%20quickly%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20men%20to%20Jamal%20and%20Habib.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20walked%20a%20short%20distance%20to%20the%20stalls%20outside%20the%20Constitution%20Club%2C%20where%20they%20first%20had%20tea%20and%20bread%20pakora%2C%20and%20also%20a%20vegetable%20patty%20each.%20Then%20after%20some%20debate%2C%20Jamal%20also%20had%20two%20gulab%20jamuns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20should%20avoid%20sugar%2C%20Jamal%20bhai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%